-- Citic Securities Seeks $1.26 Billion for Its 53% Stake in China Securities
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-29T23:52:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/citic-securities-seeks-1-26-billion-for-its-53-stake-in-china-securities.html

          
          
             Citic Securities Co. is offering to
sell its 53 percent stake in China Securities Co. for 8.59
billion yuan ($1.26 billion) on the Beijing Financial Assets
Exchange, according to filings to the exchange.  
 The brokerage is offering to sell a 45 percent stake in
China Securities for 7.29 billion yuan and another 8 percent
stake for 1.3 billion yuan, according to two separate statements
posted to the Beijing exchange. The company is seeking offers
for the stakes from June 29 to July 26, according to the
statements.  
 Citic Securities said earlier this month it was planning to
sell its stake in China Securities to meet regulatory
requirements.  
